Where: \( d \) = Sauter Mean Diameter (SMD), micrometers; \( P \) = pressure drop, psi; \( Q \) = mass flow rate, lb/hr; \( 
u_L \) = fuel kinematic viscosity, centistokes; \( 
u_G \) = gas kinematic viscosity, centistokes; \( ho_G \) = gas density, g/cm³; \( \gamma_L \) = surface tension, dyne/cm; \( F \) = fuel flow number, gal/(hr·lb·in²); \( S \propto  rac{d}{F^{1/2}} \) = dimensionless droplet size; \( R_L \propto  rac{P^{1/2} F^{1/2}}{
u_L} \) = fuel Reynolds number; \( R_G \propto  rac{P^{1/2} F^{1/2}}{
u_G} \) = gas Reynolds number; \( W \propto  rac{ho_G P F^{1/2}}{\gamma_L} \) = Weber number based on gas density.

